PROGRAM LOGIC/ PROCESSING 

The program starts and displays a welcome message for the Railway Reservation System and it presents a menu of options for different trains.
The user can choose a train by entering a number from the menu, based on the user's choice, the program creates an object of the corresponding train class (Train A, Train B, or Train C).
Then, the program displays the details of the selected train along with details including the destination and timings.

The user is prompted to enter their passenger details, including their name and age.
After the user enters their details, the program confirms that the booking has been successful.

This process will continue until the user chooses to exit the program, which is included as an option in the menu.
Once the user chooses to exit, the program prints Thank you message and terminates.
If the user enters any choice other than that included, an error message will be printed. 
